Imports are lucrative because local sugar is expensive due to high production costs occasioned by obsolete technology, low sucrose content from cane grown in the western sugar belt and mismanagement of state-owned factories.
The big question is, what will change in 2022 when the Comesa deadline comes? Would Kenya have introduced the new varieties, installed new processing technology and streamlined the factories? Or shall we be negotiating, yet again for further safeguard extensions?
